July 21 at 3:45 AM ¬∑ Centerville, IA ¬∑

I cant say enough about my swimmers!! Since May 25th when the YMCA opened back up to scheduled swims. I have had between 4 and 10 swimmers (I can have more now for staggered starts) every day for an hour. We started at 2 to 3pm and now are scheduled at 330 to 430, which it hasnt always been easy to leave work each day for an hour but I have appreciated all the kids who have wanted to keep swimming and in shape. I started HS open gyms July 1st and not one day have had an empty lane!!!

Thank you to my swim families ‚ù§üèä‚ù§
Thank you to the YMCA for keeping the facility clean and safe for us to swim!!

Last night the Centerville City Council voted to subsidize swim lessons for city youth. The City Council made a very tough decision not to open the city pool in response to COVID-19 guidelines and regulations. Even though the city pool won't be open this summer, we believe it's important to continue to provide swim lessons for our youth. Knowing how to swim is not only an important safety skill, but also a lifelong healthy activity.
Rathbun Lake Area YMCA is creating a city subsidized swim lesson program that will help meet the needs of our community while incorporating social distancing.
Our regular swim lessons will continue (with social distancing) as well.
Stay tuned for details on this new city subsidized swim lesson program.
Thank you to the Centerville City Council for supporting your YMCA in its quest to teach as many youth as possible how to swim and be safe around water!

staff will assist swimmers as they enter and exit the pool area and pool, and while swimmers from the same household are allowed to share a lane, we must limit the number of swimmers per lane to 2.

Thank you for assisting us as we follow state and local health department guidelines for your safety and the safety of our staff.

Governor Reynolds made the announcement today that many of you have been waiting for.... indoor pools will soon be allowed to reopen for lap swimming and swimming lessons! Our team at Rathbun Lake Area YMCA is preparing to reopen our pool under the current guidelines provided by state and local health officials.
*Lap swimming ONLY will be allowed on a 60 minute reservation-only basis.
*Members only will be admitted.
*Locker rooms will remain closed at this time.
*There will be no towel service.
*Physical distancing will be strictly enforced.

Please stay tuned for more updates on how to make reservations, age restrictions, etc as we work through this process. We will post our updated guidelines on our website and Facebook.

Thank you for your support and understanding!

#JustKeepSwimming
#BetterTogether

PHASE 1 OF RE-OPENING THE Y
We plan to re-open our Y with Phase 1 on May 11, 2020.
At this time our Y team members are diligently working to put into place new protocols and measures so we can resume operations in a safe manner for our members and our staff.
Details on Phase 1 (areas of the facility that will be open, who will be allowed in the facility, sanitizing procedures, social distancing rules, hours of operation, etc.) will be shared in the coming days, so please watch your email, Facebook and our website for updates.
Our virtual workouts will continue!
The pool, sauna and hot tub will remained closed in accordance with the governor's proclamation
.
As always, stay healthy in mind, body and spirit!
We are excited to see our members back at the Y (from a social distance, of course)!

Calling all ü¶∏‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏èheroes ü¶∏‚Äç‚ôÇÔ∏è staying at home with their children looking for an activity that is both challenging and educational! Gather the following:
- 1 large gallon zip lock bag
- 1 small sandwich zip lock bag
- 2 paper plates
- 2 disposable cups
- 7 toothpicks
- 1 piece foil, about 11x17
- 1 container play-dough or gak
- 2 clothespins
- 2 rubber bands
- 1 washable marker
- 1 scotch tape
- 1 straw
- yarn or twine
- 2 plastic eggs

Now the fun begins! You are stranded on an island with just these items. What can you create to help your family survive until help arrives? Work together as a team and use your creativity!

Comment with photos and descriptions of completed projects!

Most importantly HAVE FUN!
